{"id":20,"parent_id":0,"book_id":80,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":20,"title":"Chapter 17: Alma and His People Escape","subtitle":"","short_title":"Chapter 17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape"},[".heading",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.head1"},[".titleNumber","Chapter 17"],["h1","Alma and His People Escape"]],[".bodyBlock",[".image",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.f1"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_020_01.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p3"},"One day while Alma’s people were working in their fields, a Lamanite army crossed the border into their land."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p4"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/23.25"},"Mosiah 23:25"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.f2"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_020_02.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p5"},"The Nephites were frightened and ran to the city for safety. Alma told them to remember God and he would help them. The Nephites began to pray."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p6"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/23.26-28"},"Mosiah 23:26–28"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.f3"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_020_03.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p7"},"The Lord softened the hearts of the Lamanites, and they did not hurt the Nephites. The Lamanites had become lost while trying to find King Limhi’s people."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p8"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/23.29-30"},"Mosiah 23:29–30"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_020_04.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p9"},"The Lamanites promised Alma that they would not bother his people if he would tell them how to get back to their land. Alma showed them the way."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p10"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/23.36"},"Mosiah 23:36"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_020_05.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p11"},"But the Lamanites did not keep their promise. They put guards around the land, and Alma and his people were no longer free."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p12","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p12"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/23.37"},"Mosiah 23:37"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.f6"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_020_06.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p13","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p13"},"The Lamanite king made Amulon the ruler over Alma’s people. Amulon had been a Nephite and a wicked priest of King Noah."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p14","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p14"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/23.39"},"Mosiah 23:39"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/24.8-9"},"Mosiah 24:8–9"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_020_07.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p15","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p15"},"Amulon made Alma’s people work very hard. They prayed for help, but Amulon said anyone caught praying would be killed. The people continued praying in their hearts."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/24.10-12"},"Mosiah 24:10–12"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.f8"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_020_08.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p17","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p17"},"God heard their prayers and strengthened the people so their work seemed easier. The people were cheerful and patient."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p18"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/24.14-15"},"Mosiah 24:14–15"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.f9"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_020_09.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p19","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p19"},"God was pleased that the people were faithful. He told Alma that he would help them escape from the Lamanites."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/24.16-17"},"Mosiah 24:16–17"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_020_10.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p21"},"During the night the people gathered their food and animals. The next morning God kept the Lamanites asleep while Alma and his people left the city."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/24.18-20"},"Mosiah 24:18–20"]]]],[".image",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.f11"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/35666/35666_all_020_11.jpg"}],[".caption",["p.para",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p23"},"After traveling for 12 days, the people arrived at Zarahemla, where King Mosiah and his people welcomed them."]],[".citationInfo",["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/book-of-mormon-stories/chapter-17-alma-and-his-people-escape.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/24.25"},"Mosiah 24:25"]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
